HEADWORD: Muricated
<hw>Mu"ri*ca`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>muricatus</ets>, fr.
<ets>murex</ets> a pointed rock or stone.]</ety> <def>Formed with sharp
points; full of sharp points or of pickles; covered, or roughened, as a
surface, with sharp points or excrescences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

